  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sausage-and-saffron-ragu-with-fresh-orecchiette/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Add your <strong>sausage meat</strong> (remove the paper if required!) to the pan with your <strong>bay leaf[ves] </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until beginning to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sausage-and-saffron-ragu-with-fresh-orecchiette/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>fresh orecchiette</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the <strong>orecchiette</strong> for 4-6 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain, reserving a cup of the<strong> starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sausage-and-saffron-ragu-with-fresh-orecchiette/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Combine your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong>, <strong>tomato paste</strong> and <strong>saffron</strong> with 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[425ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your <strong>saffron stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sausage-and-saffron-ragu-with-fresh-orecchiette/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the sausage meat is starting to brown, add the <strong>sliced garlic</strong> to the pan and cook for 1 min further or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong> and <strong>saffron stock</strong> and cook for 2-3 min further or until the sauce thickens slightly and the sausage meat is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sausage-and-saffron-ragu-with-fresh-orecchiette/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the sauce has thickened, add a knob of <strong>butter </strong>and <strong>half</strong> your <strong>cracked black pepper</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>sausage & saffron ragù</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sausage-and-saffron-ragu-with-fresh-orecchiette/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Stir the <strong>drained orecchiette</strong> into the sauce<strong> </strong>and give everything a gentle mix up until the pasta is coated in the sauce, discard the<strong> bay leaf[ves]</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of starchy pasta water if your sauce is looking a little dry</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sausage-and-saffron-ragu-with-fresh-orecchiette/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>sausage & saffron ragù with fresh orecchiette </strong>and top with your<strong> grated Italian hard cheese </strong>and the <strong>remaining cracked black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
